We have your permission to share your Personal Data.
We believe it is important to investigate possible violations of the Terms of Service,
                                to implement those Terms of Service, or where we believe it is necessary to probe or
                                take action regarding unlawful activities, suspected fraud, or potential
                                threats against property, persons, or the methods on which we operate our Site,
                                Software, App, and/or Services.
We ascertain that the preservation, access, or disclosure of your Personal Data is
                                mandatory by law to safeguard the rights, property, or personal safety of editpad.org
                                and the users of our Site, Software, App, and/or Services, or to respond
                                to lawful requests by any public authorities.
We need to do so in relation with an acquisition, merger, reorganization, bankruptcy,
                                public offering of securities, selling of some or all of our assets. In such cases some
                                or all of your Personal Data may be transferred or shared with another
                                entity, subject to this Privacy Policy.
We may impart or disclose Non-Personal Data to third parties and publicly - for
                                example, to affiliates under agreement with us, or as part of progress reports which we
                                may provide to users.
